    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose score of 83.29 makes him the clear centerpiece of today\u2019s lineup. Facing R. Nelson, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and favorable wind conditions, positioning him to capitalize on the leadoff role. **Kyle Tucker** (72.71) and **Josh Lowe** (66.40) also emerge as Tier-1 starts; **Josh Lowe** in particular sees a surge in value due to the \"Wind Out\" factor and a favorable platoon matchup against W. Warren, while **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.22) is a mandatory start due to his elite SB potential against a slow-working Wrobleski, who allows for high-efficiency theft opportunities.\n\nStrategic depth is tested today by the decision to bench **Nasim Nunez**, who finished just outside the starting threshold with a score of 39.49. While his elite speed is tempting, the optimizer flagged the matchup against Skenes\u2014who possesses an elite 3.10 xERA and a daunting 1.89s pop-time defense\u2014as a prohibitive risk, keeping **Nasim Nunez** below our 40-point \"Zebras Floor.\" Conversely, we are navigating some volatility at the corners: **Jorge Polanco** (48.38) and **Jacob Wilson** (46.86) remain in the lineup as marginal options due to the lack of alternatives, despite facing tough arms in Wrobleski and Eovaldi. We continue to monitor the status of **Jordan Westburg**, currently on the IL, and ensure that roster stalwarts like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill** are simply resting during today's scheduled off-days for their respective clubs.",
